<div class="dablink">For the neural process, see <a href="/wiki/Confabulation_(neural_networks)" title="Confabulation (neural networks)">Confabulation (neural networks)</a>.</div>
<div class="dablink">"False memories" redirects here. For the comic book series, see <a href="/wiki/False_Memories" title="False Memories">False Memories</a>.</div>
<p><b>Confabulation</b> is the formation of false memories, perceptions, or beliefs about the self or the environment as a result of neurological or psychological dysfunction.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> When it is a matter of memory, confabulation is the confusion of <a href="/wiki/Imagination" title="Imagination">imagination</a> with <a href="/wiki/Memory" title="Memory">memory</a>, or the confused application of true memories.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
